## What is this?

A small, opinionated HTTP API on the Ramboll Python golden path: a pure,
fully-typed core (`src/{{ package_name }}/core.py`), a minimal FastAPI surface with a
`/health` endpoint (`src/{{ package_name }}/api.py`), and property-based tests. You
inherit the standards for free — focus on the domain.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Set up an environment
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate

# 2. Install the dev toolchain (includes the [api] extra: FastAPI + uvicorn)
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# 3. Run the tests (smoke + Hypothesis property tests)
pytest

# 4. Run the service
uvicorn {{ package_name }}.api:app --reload
curl localhost:8000/health
```

## Quality gates

The same three gates run locally and in CI:

```bash
pytest             # test  — smoke + property tests
ruff check . && black --check .
mypy .             # validate — lint, format, strict types
python -m build    # build — wheel + sdist (pip install build)
```

{% if layout == 'monolith' %}These commands are wired into the root smart pipeline per service — no
`.github/` directory exists at this level on purpose.
{% else %}CI references the platform's central **reusable workflows** (build / test /
validate). Updating the central workflow updates this service automatically —
never inline pipeline logic.
{% endif %}

## Testing standard

Every pure public function ships with at least one **Hypothesis property test**
(`tests/test_properties.py`) beside the example-based smoke tests
(`tests/test_smoke.py`). Properties beat examples: they cover the inputs you
didn't think of and shrink failures to minimal counterexamples.
